                        GEORGE LANGRIDGE
                   (police sergeant, N 27). I produce a certificate of the prisoner's former conviction (Read: "Clerkenwell, Nov., 1803, William Smith, convicted of stealing six bows, and other articles; 
Confined twelve months")—the prisoner is the man—I have known him from a child—he has been several times summarily convicted.





                        JOHN PARTKIDGE
                   I produce a certificate—(Read: "Central Criminal Court, John Brown, Convicted, April, 1849, of stealing a handkerchief from a man unknown, having been before convicted; 
Confined eighteen months)—Fox is the person—I was one of the witnesses—he served the eighteen months, and I was in the habit of seeing him every day.
